Conditions générales ARC-HBR
The ARC-HBR definition and all related materials are for exclusive use of health care professionals. It is intended as a supportive risk assessment tool which should not replace clinical judgment, physician–patient relationship or medical advice.
Treatment risks and benefits should always be considered in the context of a comprehensive professional clinical assessment, taking into account all available data and treatment options.
The current definition is based on expert consensus and may require modifications and recalibration as more data become available.
We assume no responsibility for how you use or interpret the ARC-HBR definition or any other information provided on this application. No data regarding patient identity will be entered, managed or stored in this application.